output: The Plum Gator 7 features a 5.7-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1440 pixels and is protected by Dragontrail Glass. It runs on Android 11 and is powered by a Mediatek MT6761V/WE chipset, coupled with a quad-core 2.0 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and PowerVR GE8300 GPU. The device comes with 32GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC, and has 3GB of RAM. It sports an 8MP main camera with LED flash and panorama features, as well as a 5MP selfie camera, and is equipped with a non-removable Li-Po 5580 mAh battery. The Plum Gator 7 also supports various connectivity options, including Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, GPS, and NFC, and is available in black and orange colors.

Chea 218 is a mobile phone featuring a TFT display with 65K colors and a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels. It supports GSM technology and operates on 2G bands, including GSM 900 and 1800. The device has a removable Li-Ion battery that provides up to 200 hours of stand-by time and up to 2 hours of talk time. Chea 218 also includes features such as SMS and MMS messaging, WAP 1.2.1 browser, and Java support. Additionally, it comes with a mini-SIM card slot and has a weight of 74 grams.

The Wiko T10 features a 6.5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels and a screen-to-body ratio of approximately 82.1%. It runs on Android 11 (Go edition) and is powered by a Mediatek MT6761 Helio A22 chipset, coupled with a Quad-core 2.0 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and PowerVR GE8300 GPU. The device comes equipped with a single 13 MP main camera that supports LED flash, panorama, and 1080p video recording at 30fps, as well as a 5 MP selfie camera. It offers various connectivity options, including Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, GPS, and FM radio, and is available in two colors: Black and Green. The Wiko T10 is fueled by a non-removable Li-Ion 5000 mAh battery and has a dual SIM slot that supports Nano-SIM cards.

Vodafone Tab Prime 7 offers a display size of 10.1 inches with a resolution of 1200x1920 pixels. The device features a 5MP camera and supports video recording. It runs on Android 6.0 (Marshmallow) operating system, powered by Qualcomm MSM8937 Snapdragon 430 chipset and an octa-core CPU. The tablet comes with 2GB RAM and 16GB internal storage, which can be expanded using a microSDXC card. The device is equipped with a non-removable Li-Po 5830 mAh battery and supports various connectivity options, including Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and GPS.

Parla Sonic 3.5S features a 3.5-inch TFT display with a resolution of 320 x 480 pixels and supports up to 256K colors. The device runs on Android 4.4 (KitKat) operating system and is powered by a Spreadtrum 7715 chipset, paired with a 1.0 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and Mali-400 GPU. It has a 2 MP primary camera with LED flash and HDR capabilities, and can record videos at 480p@30fps. The phone supports dual SIM functionality, with mini-SIM and micro-SIM compatibility, and offers connectivity options such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 2.1, and microUSB 2.0. It is fueled by a removable Li-Ion 1300 mAh battery, which provides up to 171 hours of standby time and up to 3 hours 30 minutes of talk time.

The Innostream INNO 30 features a TFT display with 256K colors and a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels. It has a VGA camera and supports video recording. The device comes with a removable Li-Ion battery that provides up to 150 hours of standby time and up to 3-5 hours of talk time. The INNO 30 also includes features such as SMS, MMS, and email messaging, as well as a WAP browser and games. Additionally, it supports downloadable polyphonic and MP3 ringtones and has a phonebook capacity of 800 entries.

The MIO Leap K1 features a 2.6-inch TFT resistive touchscreen display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels and supports 65K colors. It runs on Windows Mobile 6.1 Professional and is powered by a Samsung S3C 2443 processor with a clock speed of 400MHz. The device includes a 2-megapixel camera with autofocus and LED flash, and also has a secondary OLED display. In terms of connectivity, the MIO Leap K1 supports Bluetooth 2.0, GPS, and miniUSB 1.1, but does not have Wi-Fi or a 3.5mm audio jack. The phone is powered by a removable Li-Ion 790 mAh battery, which provides up to 5 hours of talk time.
